@startuml cgs-kvk-company-changes
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  COMPANY CHANGES — KVK / NHR Flow Through CGS
'  What happens when a company registers, moves, or changes?
'  Real data from igp_ontwikkel_cgs_owner database
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **What Happens in CGS When a Company Changes?**\nComplete flow: KVK (Chamber of Commerce) → CGS → Municipal Systems\n<size:10>11 KVK/NHR services | 3 KVK signal types | Namespace: schemas.kvk.nl + kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr</size>

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequenceBoxBorderColor #90A4AE

actor "Company\nOwner" as owner
participant "**KVK**\n//Kamer van\nKoophandel//\n(Chamber of\nCommerce)" as kvk #F0F4C3

box "CGS Service Bus" #E3F2FD
  participant "**Authorization**\n//serviceusage//" as auth #BBDEFB
  participant "**Message\nMatching**\n//messagedefinition//" as match #BBDEFB
  participant "**Router**\n//channeldefinition//" as router #90CAF9
end box

participant "**CML**\n//Broker\nNational//\n(Landelijke\nVoorzieningen)" as cml #E1BEE7

participant "**CIR / CIR_NODE**\n//Company\nRegistry//\n(Inschrijving\nRegister)" as cir #FFF9C4

participant "**CMG**\n//Broker\nData//\n(Distributie)" as cmg #E1BEE7

note over kvk
  **KVK = Kamer van Koophandel**
  (Dutch Chamber of Commerce)
  
  National registry of all companies,
  foundations, and associations.
  
  **NHR = Nieuw Handelsregister**
  (New Trade Register) — the
  standardized data exchange format.
  
  **HR = Handelsregister**
  (Trade Register) — query interface.
end note

== **SCENARIO 1: Company registers a new branch or changes address** ==

owner -> kvk : Registers change at KVK:\n• New branch location\n• Address change\n• Name change\n• New registration

note over kvk
  KVK sends a **signal** (signaal)
  to the municipality via CGS.
  
  Three types of signals:
end note

== **FLOW A: KVKMutatieService (ASYNC) — KVK sends mutation signal** ==

kvk -[#33691E,bold]> auth : **SignaalGewijzigdeInschrijving**\nnamespace: schemas.kvk.nl/.../gewijzigdeinschrijving/2023/01\nprotocol: **WEBSERVICE** (SOAP)\nvia adapter: STUF0301WSINADAPTER

note right of auth
  **3 signal message types:**
  
  1. **SignaalNieuweInschrijving**
     ""schemas.kvk.nl/.../nieuweinschrijving/2023/01""
     → A brand new company registered
  
  2. **SignaalGewijzigdeInschrijving**
     ""schemas.kvk.nl/.../gewijzigdeinschrijving/2023/01""
     → Existing company changed (name, owner, etc.)
  
  3. **SignaalGewijzigdeVestiging**
     ""schemas.kvk.nl/.../gewijzigdevestiging/2024/01""
     → Branch/location changed (address, activity)
  
  **Response:** Bv03Bericht (StUF 0301)
  **Fault:** Fo02Bericht (StUF 0301)
end note

auth -> auth : Check: Is KVK authorized?\n✅ Yes (serviceusage)

auth --> kvk : **Bv03Bericht** (StUF 0301)\n"Signal received"

auth -> match : Forward signal
match -> match : Match by namespace:\nschemas.kvk.nl → KVK mutation

note over match
  **KVKMutatieService** = ASYNC
  The signal only says "something changed"
  — the actual data must be fetched separately.
  
  This triggers CML to pull the full details
  from KVK's API.
end note

match -> router : Route to CML
router -[#6A1B9A,bold]> cml : Signal forwarded\n(no channel routing —\nCML handles internally)

== **FLOW B: KVKEventService (ASYNC) — Internal event processing** ==

cml -[#6A1B9A]> auth : **KVKEventService**\nSame 3 signal types\nvia **Java** adapter (JAVAGENERICINADAPTER)\nor **WEBSERVICE** (STUF0301WSINADAPTER)

note right of auth
  **KVKEventService** is also called by:
  • **CML** (Broker National)
  • **CIR_NODE** (Company Registry)
  
  Same signals, but now processed
  internally within the MKS platform.
  
  **Response:** Bv03Bericht
  **Fault:** Fo03Bericht
end note

auth --> cml : Bv03Bericht

== **FLOW C: CML fetches full company data from KVK** ==

note over cml
  CML now calls KVK's API to get
  the **complete company record**
  (not just the signal).
  
  This happens via **StUFBeantwoordVraagHR**
  (synchronous query service).
end note

cml -[#1565C0,bold]> auth : **StUFBeantwoordVraagHR** [SYN]\n**ophalenInschrijvingRequest**\nnamespace: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/kvk0300\n"Give me full details of KVK# 12345678"

auth -> match : Authorized ✅ (CML, CIR, CIR_NODE)
match -> router : Match: ophalenInschrijving
router -[#1565C0,bold]> kvk : **WEBSERVICE** out\nadapters: NHR30INSWSOUTADAPTER\nor NHR30CLIQINSWSOUTADAPTER\nendpoint: NHRSTUFSYN\n\n→ Query goes to **KVK national API**

kvk --> router : **ophalenInschrijvingResponse**\nFull company data:\n• KVK number\n• Company name\n• Legal form\n• All branches\n• Activities (SBI codes)\n• Registered persons

router --> cml : Response forwarded

|||

cml -[#1565C0]> auth : **StUFBeantwoordVraagHR** [SYN]\n**ophalenVestigingRequest**\nnamespace: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/kvk0300\n"Give me branch details"

auth -> router
router -[#1565C0]> kvk : WEBSERVICE out\nadapter: NHR30VESWSOUTADAPTER\nor NHR30CLIQVESWSOUTADAPTER

kvk --> router : **ophalenVestigingResponse**\nBranch details:\n• Visiting address\n• Postal address\n• Phone, email\n• Branch activities

router --> cml : Response forwarded

note over cml
  CML now has the complete
  company data from KVK.
  
  **Next step:** Store it in the
  municipal systems and convert
  to StUF-BG format if needed.
end note

== **FLOW D: Store company data in municipal registry** ==

cml -[#6A1B9A,bold]> auth : **VerwerkNHRBericht** [SYN]\nnamespace: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/0300\n"Process this NHR record"

auth -> match
match -> router : Route to CIR
router -[#6A1B9A,bold]> cir : **JAVA** out\nendpoint: CIR\nprotocol: Java internal\n\nCIR stores the company\ndata in municipal registry

cir --> router : Response
router --> cml : ✅ Stored

|||

cml -[#6A1B9A]> auth : **OpslaanNHR2BGService** [SYN]\n**genereerProductRespons**\nnamespace: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/0300\n"Convert NHR data to BG format\nand store as person/address"

note right of auth
  **Why NHR→BG conversion?**
  
  Company owners (natuurlijk persoon)
  need to exist in the BG (person)
  registry too. This service converts
  NHR company data into StUF-BG
  person records so the municipality
  has a unified view.
end note

auth -> router
router -> cir : JAVA → CIR

|||

cml -[#6A1B9A]> auth : **OpslaanNHRPlusService** [SYN]\n**genereerProductRespons**\nnamespace: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/0300\n"Store extended NHR data"

auth -> router

|||

cml -[#6A1B9A]> auth : **OpslaanMaatschappelijkeActiviteitService** [SYN]\n**genereerProductRespons**\nnamespace: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/0300\n"Store business activity records"

note right of auth
  **Maatschappelijke Activiteit** =
  "Societal Activity" — the legal
  entity behind the company.
  
  Called by: **CIR_NODE**, **CML**, **ZGS_SSL**
end note

auth -> router
router -> cir : JAVA → CIR

== **FLOW E: Data quality & maintenance** ==

cml -[#546E7A]> auth : **KwaliteitBedrijvenService** [SYN]\n**kwaliteitBedrijvenRequest**\nnamespace: makelaarsuite.nl/kwaliteitBedrijven/0100\n"Check data quality of company records"

auth -> router
router -> cmg : **JAVA** → CMGDISTRIBUTIE\nCMG checks data quality\nand returns report

cmg --> router : **kwaliteitBedrijvenResponse**
router --> cml : Quality report

|||

cml -[#546E7A]> auth : **OpschonenBedrijvenService** [SYN]\n**opschonenBedrijven**\nnamespace: civision.nl/CGS/clean\n"Clean up stale company records"

auth -> router
router -> cir : **JAVA** → CIR\nRemove outdated records

cir --> router : **Bv04Bericht** (confirmation)
router --> cml : ✅ Cleaned

== **FLOW F: Other apps query company data** ==

note over auth, router
  **After company data is stored, any authorized app can query it:**
end note

cir -[#1565C0]> auth : **StUFBeantwoordVraagNHR** [SYN]\nvraagBericht (nhr)\n"Query company by KVK number or name"

note right of auth
  **StUFBeantwoordVraagNHR** consumers:
  • CIR, CIR_NODE, CML
  
  **StUFBeantwoordVraagNHRPLUS** consumers:
  • CIR_NODE, CML
  (extended NHR data)
  
  Routes to **NHR** provider via
  WEBSERVICE (NHRSTUFSYN / NHRDIGSTUFSYN)
  — currently inactive channels,
  queries served from local CIR cache.
end note

auth -> router
router --> cir : synchroonAntwoordBericht\nwith company data

@enduml


@startuml cgs-kvk-overview
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  KVK/NHR — Bird's Eye Overview
'  All 11 services and their relationships
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **KVK / Company Changes — All Services & Message Flows**\n//11 services, 3 signal types, 5 query types, 3 storage operations//

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 25
skinparam ranksep 20

' === EXTERNAL ===
component "**KVK**\n//Kamer van Koophandel//\n(National Chamber\nof Commerce)" as kvk #F0F4C3

' === INCOMING SIGNALS ===
package "**Step 1: KVK Signals**\n\"Something changed at a company\"" as signals_pkg #FFF3E0 {

  component "**KVKMutatieService** [ASYNC]\n\n**Messages IN (from KVK):**\n• SignaalNieuweInschrijving\n  (new company registration)\n• SignaalGewijzigdeInschrijving\n  (company data changed)\n• SignaalGewijzigdeVestiging\n  (branch/location changed)\n\n**Response:** Bv03Bericht\n**Fault:** Fo02Bericht\n**Consumers:** KVK" as svc_mutatie #FFE0B2

  component "**KVKEventService** [ASYNC]\n\nSame 3 signal types\n(internal event processing)\n\n**Response:** Bv03Bericht\n**Fault:** Fo03Bericht\n**Consumers:** KVK, CML, CIR_NODE" as svc_event #FFE0B2
}

' === QUERIES TO KVK ===
package "**Step 2: Fetch Full Data from KVK**\n\"Give me the complete company record\"" as queries_pkg #E3F2FD {

  component "**StUFBeantwoordVraagHR** [SYN]\n\n**ophalenInschrijvingRequest**\n→ ophalenInschrijvingResponse\n(full company record)\n\n**ophalenVestigingRequest**\n→ ophalenVestigingResponse\n(branch details)\n\nns: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/kvk0300\n**Consumers:** CIR, CIR_NODE, CML\n**Provider:** KVK (4 WS adapters)" as svc_hr #BBDEFB

  component "**StUFBeantwoordVraagNHR** [SYN]\n\nvraagBericht (nhr format)\n→ synchroonAntwoordBericht\n\n**Consumers:** CIR, CIR_NODE, CML\n**Provider:** NHR (inactive channels)" as svc_nhr #BBDEFB

  component "**StUFBeantwoordVraagNHRPLUS** [SYN]\n\nExtended NHR data query\n\n**Consumers:** CIR_NODE, CML" as svc_nhr_plus #BBDEFB
}

' === STORAGE ===
package "**Step 3: Store in Municipal Systems**\n\"Save company data locally\"" as store_pkg #E8F5E9 {

  component "**VerwerkNHRBericht** [SYN]\n\nProcess NHR record\nns: kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/0300\n\n**Consumers:** CML, KVK\n**Provider:** CIR (Java)" as svc_verwerk #C8E6C9

  component "**OpslaanNHR2BGService** [SYN]\n\ngenereerProductRespons\n→ Convert NHR → StUF-BG\n(company owners as persons)\n\n**Consumers:** CIR_NODE, CML\n**Provider:** (no active channel)" as svc_nhr2bg #C8E6C9

  component "**OpslaanNHRPlusService** [SYN]\n\ngenereerProductRespons\nStore extended NHR data\n\n**Consumers:** CIR_NODE, CML" as svc_nhrplus #C8E6C9

  component "**OpslaanMaatschappelijke-\nActiviteitService** [SYN]\n\ngenereerProductRespons\nStore business activity\n(legal entity records)\n\n**Consumers:** CIR_NODE, CML, ZGS_SSL\n**Provider:** CIR (Java)" as svc_maatsch #C8E6C9
}

' === MAINTENANCE ===
package "**Step 4: Data Quality**\n\"Keep company data clean\"" as maint_pkg #F3E5F5 {

  component "**KwaliteitBedrijvenService** [SYN]\n\nkwaliteitBedrijvenRequest\n→ kwaliteitBedrijvenResponse\nns: makelaarsuite.nl/kwaliteitBedrijven\n\n**Consumer:** CML\n**Provider:** CMG (Java)" as svc_kwaliteit #E1BEE7

  component "**OpschonenBedrijvenService** [SYN]\n\nopschonenBedrijven\n→ Bv04Bericht\nns: civision.nl/CGS/clean\n\n**Consumer:** CML\n**Provider:** CIR (Java)" as svc_opschonen #E1BEE7
}

' === KEY APPS ===
component "**CML**\n//Broker National//\nOrchestrates entire\nKVK flow" as cml #E1BEE7
component "**CIR / CIR_NODE**\n//Company Registry//\nStores & serves\ncompany data" as cir #FFF9C4
component "**CMG**\n//Broker Data//\nData distribution\n& quality" as cmg #E1BEE7

' === CONNECTIONS ===
' Signals
kvk -[#E65100,bold]-> svc_mutatie : 3 signal types\n(WEBSERVICE)
svc_mutatie -[#E65100]-> cml : triggers fetch
kvk -[#E65100]-> svc_event
cml -[#E65100]-> svc_event : Java internal
cir -[#E65100]-> svc_event : Java internal

' Queries to KVK
cml -[#1565C0,bold]-> svc_hr : fetch full data
svc_hr -[#1565C0,bold]-> kvk : WEBSERVICE\n(4 out-adapters)
cml -[#1565C0]-> svc_nhr
cml -[#1565C0]-> svc_nhr_plus
cir -[#1565C0]-> svc_nhr : query local cache

' Storage
cml -[#2E7D32,bold]-> svc_verwerk : store NHR
svc_verwerk -[#2E7D32]-> cir : Java → CIR
cml -[#2E7D32]-> svc_nhr2bg : convert NHR→BG
cml -[#2E7D32]-> svc_nhrplus : store extended
cml -[#2E7D32]-> svc_maatsch : store activities
svc_maatsch -[#2E7D32]-> cir : Java → CIR

' Maintenance
cml -[#6A1B9A]-> svc_kwaliteit : check quality
svc_kwaliteit -[#6A1B9A]-> cmg : Java → CMG
cml -[#6A1B9A]-> svc_opschonen : clean up
svc_opschonen -[#6A1B9A]-> cir : Java → CIR

legend bottom left
  **The complete KVK flow in 4 steps:**
  
  1. **Signal** — KVK tells CGS "a company changed"
     (3 signal types via KVKMutatieService / KVKEventService)
  
  2. **Fetch** — CML queries KVK for full company data
     (StUFBeantwoordVraagHR: inschrijving + vestiging queries)
  
  3. **Store** — CML saves data in municipal systems
     (VerwerkNHRBericht → CIR, OpslaanNHR2BG → convert to persons,
      OpslaanMaatschappelijkeActiviteitService → legal entities)
  
  4. **Maintain** — CML keeps data clean over time
     (KwaliteitBedrijvenService, OpschonenBedrijvenService)
  
  **Key namespace: http://www.kvk.nl/StUF/sector/hr/kvk0300**
endlegend

@enduml
